<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse otstarve </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse otstarve on vaba ettev&otilde;tluse huvidest l&auml;htuv konkurentsivabaduse kaitsmine loodusvarade ammutamisel, toodete valmistamisel ja teenuste osutamisel ning toodete ja teenuste (edaspidi kaubad) ostmisel ja m&uuml;&uuml;misel ning muus majandustegevuses konkurentsivabaduse kahjustamise &auml;rahoidmine ja k&otilde;rvaldamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The purpose of this Act is to safeguard free competition upon the extraction of natural resources, manufacture of goods, provision of services, sale and purchase of products and services (hereinafter goods), and to prevent and eliminate the restriction of competition in other economic activities based on the interests of free enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse ka juhul, kui konkurentsivabaduse kahjustamisele suunatud tegu v&otilde;i tegevusetus toimub v&auml;ljaspool Eesti territooriumi, kuid kahjustab konkurentsivabadust Eesti territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act also applies if the action or omission directed at restricting competition takes place outside the territory of Estonia but restricts competition in the territory of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse subjektid </eesti>
<inglise>Subjects of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse subjektiks on ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The subjects of this Act are undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seadusega ettev&otilde;tjale rakendatavad s&auml;tted laienevad ka kaubaturul osalevale v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tjate huvides tegutsevale mittetulundus&uuml;hingule, sihtasutusele v&otilde;i teisele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions applicable to undertakings pursuant to this Act also extend to non-profit associations, foundations and other persons who participate in a market or act in the interests of undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tted laienevad riigiasutustele ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutustele, kui nimetatud asutuste otsuse v&otilde;i tegevuse kaudu kahjustatakse konkurentsivabadust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of this Act extend to state agencies and local government agencies if the decisions or activities of such agencies restrict competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses loetakse &uuml;heks ettev&otilde;tjaks &uuml;hte kontserni kuuluvaid ettev&otilde;tjaid v&otilde;i teisi valitseva m&otilde;ju kaudu &uuml;ksteisega seotud ettev&otilde;tjaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the purposes of this Act, undertakings which belong to the same group of companies or other undertakings which are connected through control are deemed to be one undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses loetakse valitsevaks m&otilde;juks teise ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) For the purposes of this Act, the following are deemed to be control over another undertaking: </inglise>
<eesti>1) emaettev&otilde;tja kontrolli t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>1) control of a parent company over a subsidiary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) olukorda, kus ettev&otilde;tja omab &otilde;igust nimetada v&otilde;i tagasi kutsuda enamust teise ettev&otilde;tja juhtorganite liikmetest v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>2) a situation where an undertaking has the right to appoint or remove a majority of the members of the directing bodies of another undertaking; or </inglise>
<eesti>3) olukorda, kus ettev&otilde;tja omab h&auml;&auml;lteenamust teise ettev&otilde;tja juures kokkuleppe alusel koos m&otilde;ne oma aktsion&auml;ri v&otilde;i osanikuga. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a situation where an undertaking, by an agreement and together with some of its stockholders or shareholders, has a majority of votes in another undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevat seadust rakendatakse kaubaturul osalevate v&otilde;i osaleda soovivate isikute vahelise konkurentsivabaduse kaitseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act is applied to safeguard competition between persons who participate or intend to participate in a market. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaubaturg on hinna, kvaliteedi, tehniliste omaduste, realiseerimis- ning kasutustingimuste, tarbimis- ja muude omaduste poolest ostja seisukohalt omavahel asendatavate kaupade k&auml;ibimise ala kogu Eesti territooriumil v&otilde;i selle osal. </eesti>
<inglise>A market is an area in the whole territory of Estonia or a part thereof in which goods which are regarded as interchangeable by the buyer by reason of price, quality, technical characteristics, conditions of sale or use, consumption or other characteristics are circulated. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus piiritleda kaubaturg iga konkreetse kauba osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Competition Board has the right to define the market for each specific good. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppe ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on Agreements and Concerted Practices </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsivabadust kahjustava kokkuleppe ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on agreements and concerted practices which restrict competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Leping, muu tehing ja kokkulepe (edaspidi kokkulepe) v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus, mis on vaba ettev&otilde;tlust kahjustava ja konkurentsivabadust piirava, takistava, kitsendava v&otilde;i moonutava eesm&auml;rgi v&otilde;i tagaj&auml;rjega, on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Contracts, other transactions and agreements (hereinafter agreements) or concerted practices which have as their object or effect the restriction, prevention, limitation or distortion of free enterprise and competition are prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud kokkulepet v&otilde;i tegevust loetakse konkurentsivabadust kahjustavaks, kui sellega otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt: </eesti>
<inglise>Such agreements or activities are deemed to restrict competition if they directly or indirectly: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks hinnakujundamise tingimust, sealhulgas kolmanda isiku suhtes kohaldatavat kauba ostu- v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;gihinda, tariifi, juurde- v&otilde;i mahahindlust, intressim&auml;&auml;ra, renti v&otilde;i &uuml;&uuml;ri; </eesti>
<inglise>1) fix pricing conditions, including the purchase or selling prices of goods, tariffs, mark-ups, rebates, interest rates, rent or lease payments to be applied to a third person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) piiratakse tootmist, kaubaturgu, tehnilist arengut v&otilde;i investeeringut; </eesti>
<inglise>2) limit production, markets, technical development or investment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) jagatakse kaubaturgu, sealhulgas varustusallikat; </eesti>
<inglise>3) share markets, including sources of supply; </inglise>
<eesti>4) piiratakse kolmanda isiku kaubaturule p&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;i p&uuml;&uuml;takse teda kaubaturult v&auml;lja t&otilde;rjuda; </eesti>
<inglise>4) restrict access to markets to third persons or attempt to exclude third persons from markets; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vahetatakse konkurentsivabadust kahjustavat teavet; </eesti>
<inglise>5) disseminate information which distorts competition; </inglise>
<eesti>6) rakendatakse erinevat tingimust v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsete kokkulepete puhul kolmanda ettev&otilde;tjaga, pannes ta sellega kas soodsamasse v&otilde;i ebasoodsamasse konkurentsiolukorda; </eesti>
<inglise>6) apply dissimilar conditions to equivalent agreements with third undertakings, thereby placing them at a competitive advantage or disadvantage; </inglise>
<eesti>7) seatakse kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimise eelduseks teise poole n&otilde;usolek v&otilde;tta endale t&auml;iendav kohustus, mis oma iseloomult v&otilde;i &auml;ritava kohaselt ei ole seotud sellise kokkuleppega v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>7) make the entry into agreements subject to acceptance by the other parties of supplementary obligations which, by their nature or according to commercial usage, have no connection with such agreements; or </inglise>
<eesti>8) kahjustatakse konkurentsivabadust k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1-7 nimetamata viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>8) restrict competition in a manner not specified in clauses 1) -7) of this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppe ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse lubatavus </eesti>
<inglise>Permissibility of agreements and concerted practices </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kokkulepet v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevust ei loeta vaba ettev&otilde;tlust kahjustada v&otilde;ivaks konkurentsivabadust piiravaks, takistavaks, kitsendavaks v&otilde;i moonutavaks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Agreements or concerted practices are deemed not to restrict, prevent, limit or distort competition such that free enterprise may be distorted if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kokkulepet s&otilde;lmivate v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevust arendavate poolte k&auml;ivete summaarne osat&auml;htsus ei ole kokkuleppest v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevusest m&otilde;jutatud kaubaturul suurem kui viis protsenti ja </eesti>
<inglise>1) the combined significance of the parties entering into an agreement or developing concerted practices does not exceed 5 per cent of the turnover of the market influenced by such agreement or concerted practices; and </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tja poolt mitme teise ettev&otilde;tjaga s&otilde;lmitud sarnaste kokkulepete, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevust arendavate poolte k&auml;ivete summaarne osat&auml;htsus ei ole kokkuleppest v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevusest m&otilde;jutatud kaubaturul suurem kui viis protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the combined significance of similar agreements entered into by an undertaking with several other undertakings or of concerted practices of such parties does not exceed 5 per cent of the turnover of the market influenced by such agreements or concerted practices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 tingimused peavad olema t&auml;idetud kogu kokkuleppe v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse kestuse jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The conditions of subsection (1) of this section shall be fulfilled during the entire term of the agreement or concerted practices. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandid </eesti>
<inglise>Exemptions </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib oma otsusega ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel anda erandi k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 nimetatud kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimiseks, kui see: </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of an undertaking, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may grant by a decision an exemption in respect of entry into an agreement specified in &sect; 4 of this Act if such agreement: </inglise>
<eesti>1) aitab kaasa teenindamise v&otilde;i kaupade tootmise v&otilde;i levitamise parandamisele, keskkonna kaitsmisele v&otilde;i tehnilise v&otilde;i majandusliku progressi edendamisele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) contributes to improving the supply of services or production or distribution of goods, protecting the environment or promoting technical or economic progress; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&otilde;imaldab tarbijatel saada sellest tulenevast kasust &otilde;iglast osa; </eesti>
<inglise>2) allows consumers a fair share of the resulting benefit; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei too kolmandatele isikutele kaasa kitsendusi, mis ei ole h&auml;davajalikud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punktis 1 nimetatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamisel, ja </eesti>
<inglise>3) does not bring about restrictions on third persons which are not indispensable to the attainment of the objectives specified in clause 1) of this section, and </inglise>
<eesti>4) ei too kaasa olulist konkurentsivabaduse kahjustamist kaubaturul. </eesti>
<inglise>4) does not bring about a substantial restriction of competition in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Grupierandid </eesti>
<inglise>Block exemptions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Grupierandiks on rahandusministri ettepanekul Vabariigi Valitsuse antud luba s&otilde;lmida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustele vastavaid teatud &uuml;hte liiki konkurentsivabadust kahjustavaid v&otilde;i kahjustada v&otilde;ivaid kokkuleppeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Block exemptions are permission granted by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Finance to enter into a certain category of agreement which complies with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act and restricts or may restrict competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Grupierand kehtestatakse t&auml;htajalisena ja see m&auml;&auml;rab: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A block exemption is established for a specified term and determines: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kokkuleppe liigi nimetuse, mille suhtes grupierand kohaldub; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the category of agreement to which the block exemption applies; </inglise>
<eesti>2) piirangud v&otilde;i tingimused, mis sellistes kokkulepetes ei tohi sisalduda; </eesti>
<inglise>2) restrictions or conditions which shall not be included in such agreements; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tingimused, mis peavad sellistes kokkulepetes sisalduma, ning piirangud ja tingimused, mis v&otilde;ivad sellistes kokkulepetes sisalduda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) conditions which must be included in such agreements, and restrictions and conditions which may be included in such agreements; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muud tingimused, millele sellised kokkulepped peavad vastama. </eesti>
<inglise>4) other conditions which such agreements shall comply with. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel antud grupierand ei kohaldu kokkulepete suhtes j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A block exemption granted on the basis of subsection (1) of this section does not apply to an agreement if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kui kokkulepe v&otilde;i selle tingimus on k&auml;sitletav k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 14 s&auml;testatud kaubaturgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja seisundi kuritarvitamisena; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the agreement or a condition thereof is considered an abuse by an undertaking of a dominant position within the market, provided for in &sect; 14 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui kaubaturul, mida antud kokkulepe m&otilde;jutab, praktiliselt puudub konkurents kokkuleppepoole v&otilde;i -poolte jaoks &uuml;hiselt. </eesti>
<inglise>2) competition is virtually non-existent in the market influenced by the agreement for a party to the agreement or the parties to the agreement jointly. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsivabadust kahjustavate kokkulepete kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Invalidity of agreements restricting competition </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkulepped v&otilde;i nende tingimused, millel on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 m&auml;rgitud eesm&auml;rgid v&otilde;i tagaj&auml;rjed ning millele pole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 6 v&otilde;i 7 alusel antud erandit, on t&uuml;hised, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 5 vastavad kokkulepped v&otilde;i nende tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>Agreements or conditions thereof which have as their object or effect that specified in &sect; 4 of this Act and which are not granted an exemption on the basis of &sect; 6 or 7 of this Act are void, except agreements or conditions thereof which comply with &sect; 5 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotlus </eesti>
<inglise>Application for Exemption </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotluse esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Submission of application for exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud erandi saamiseks tuleb Konkurentsiametile esitada taotlus enne kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimist v&otilde;i kuue kuu jooksul erandit vajava kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to obtain an exemption provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act, an application shall be submitted to the Competition Board before entry into an agreement or within six months after entry into an agreement which requires an exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastav kokkulepe v&otilde;i selle konkurentsivabadust kahjustav tingimus on kuni erandi andmiseni kehtetu. </eesti>
<inglise>Such agreement or a condition thereof which restricts competition is invalid until the exemption is granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eranditaotlus kokkuleppe kohta, mis ei olnud selle s&otilde;lmimisel k&auml;esoleva seadusega vastuolus, tuleb esitada kolme kuu jooksul, alates nende asjaolude ilmnemisest, mille t&otilde;ttu kokkulepe v&otilde;i selle tingimus osutub seadusega vastuolus olevaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for an exemption concerning an agreement which was not contrary to this Act at the time of entry into such agreement shall be submitted within three months after circumstances due to which the agreement or a condition thereof is contrary to this Act, become evident. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastav kokkulepe v&otilde;i selle tingimus on vastavate asjaolude ilmnemisest kuni erandi andmiseni kehtetu. </eesti>
<inglise>Such agreement or condition thereof is invalid from the time the circumstances become evident until the exemption is granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eranditaotluse esitab kokkuleppe &uuml;ks pool v&otilde;i pooled &uuml;hiselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) One party or the parties to the agreement jointly shall submit an application for exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eranditaotluse esitaja v&otilde;i esitatud eranditaotluse aluseks oleva kokkuleppe teine pool v&otilde;ib eranditaotluse igal ajal kuni erandi andmiseni tagasi v&otilde;tta, esitades sellekohase kirjaliku avalduse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant for exemption or the other party to the agreement which is the basis of a submitted application for exemption may withdraw the application for exemption at any time until the exemption is granted, by submission of a written application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotlusele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for application for exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametile esitatakse eranditaotlus koos kogu vajaliku teabega vastavalt rahandusministri poolt kehtestatavale juhendile, kusjuures Konkurentsiameti n&otilde;udmisel peab andma selgitusi ning esitama tutvumiseks dokumentide originaalid v&otilde;i nende koopiad v&otilde;i &auml;rakirjad, mille originaalilevastavust kinnitab nende esitaja oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An application for exemption shall be submitted to the Competition Board together with all necessary information in accordance with the instructions established by the Minister of Finance, whereupon, at the request of the Competition Board, explanations shall be given and the originals of documents or copies or transcripts thereof shall be submitted for examination, the authenticity of which shall be confirmed by the signature of the submitter. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui eranditaotluses sisalduv v&otilde;i sellega seoses esitatud teave on mittet&auml;ielik, eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i eksitav, teatab Konkurentsiamet sellest taotlejale kirjalikult, n&otilde;udes kogu teabe esitamist ja m&auml;&auml;rates selle esitamiseks t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If information contained in an application for exemption or information relating to the application is incomplete, incorrect or misleading, the Competition Board shall notify the applicant thereof in writing and shall demand submission of all information and determine a deadline for submission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud juhul algavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 11 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajad kogu teabe laekumise kohta Konkurentsiameti poolt taotluse esitajale sellekohase kirjaliku teate saatmise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the terms provided for in &sect; 11 of this Act shall commence from the date the Competition Board sends a written notice to the applicant confirming receipt of all information. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isik, kelle kasuks on erand antud, ja isik, kes erandi andmise otsust taotleb, peab eranditaotluses esitatud andmete olulistest muudatustest teatama Konkurentsiametile v&auml;hemalt seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul vastava teabe saamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The person for whose benefit an exemption is granted and the person who applies for the decision to grant an exemption shall notify the Competition Board of substantial changes in the information presented in the application for exemption within seven calendar days after receipt of the relevant information. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teabe juurde, mida eranditaotluse esitaja peab &auml;risaladuseks, teeb ta vastava m&auml;rke v&otilde;i annab selle teabe eraldi lisana. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant for exemption shall designate information he or she deems to be a business secret or shall submit such information separately as an annex. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;risaladuseks ei saa olla &uuml;ldsusele avaldamisele kuuluv teave. </eesti>
<inglise>Information subject to public disclosure is not a business secret. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotluse lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Processing of application for exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb eranditaotluse kohta &uuml;he j&auml;rgnevatest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make one of the following decisions concerning an application for exemption: </inglise>
<eesti>1) annab erandi, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks olev kokkulepe on vastavuses k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to grant the exemption if he or she finds that the agreement which is the basis of the application complies with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) keeldub erandi andmisest, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks olev kokkulepe ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to refuse the exemption if he or she finds that the agreement which is the basis of the application does not comply with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) algatab eranditaotluse kohta t&auml;iendava menetluse, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks oleva kokkuleppe sobivus erandi saamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 alusel on kaheldav ning otsuse langetamiseks erandi andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta on vajalik saada t&auml;iendavat teavet v&otilde;i teostada t&auml;iendavat kontrolli; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to initiate supplementary proceedings concerning the application for exemption if he or she finds that it is doubtful whether the agreement which is the basis for the grant of exemption pursuant to &sect; 6 of this Act qualifies for an exemption and it is necessary to obtain additional information or conduct a supplementary examination in order to decide to grant or refuse the exemption; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tunnistab kokkuleppe erandit mittevajavaks, kui ta leiab, et tegemist ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 s&auml;testatud kokkuleppega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to declare that the agreement does not require an exemption if he or she finds that the agreement is not an agreement provided for in &sect; 4 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) l&otilde;petab menetluse erandit andmata, kui kokkulepe ei vaja erandit k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 5 toodud alustel v&otilde;i kui seda liiki kokkulepetele on antud grupierand v&otilde;i kui eranditaotlus on tagasi v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kui eranditaotluse esitaja v&otilde;i kokkuleppe teine pool ei ole esitanud kogu vajalikku teavet Konkurentsiameti poolt selleks teistkordselt m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) to terminate the proceedings without granting an exemption if the agreement does not require an exemption on the bases provided for in &sect; 5 of this Act or if a block exemption has been granted to the category of agreement, the application for exemption is withdrawn, or the applicant for exemption or the other party to the agreement has not submitted all necessary information by the deadline specified therefor by the Competition Board for a second time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb &uuml;he k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud otsustest kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast kogu teabe esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make one of the decisions provided for in clauses (1) 1) or 2) of this section within two months after submission of all information. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsustab algatada t&auml;iendava menetluse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 3 alusel, teatab ta sellest kirjalikult erandi taotlejatele ning teeb l&otilde;pliku otsuse erandi andmise, sellest keeldumise v&otilde;i erandi mittevajalikkuse kohta kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast t&auml;ieliku teabe esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy decides to commence supplementary proceedings on the basis of clause (1) 3) of this section, he or she shall notify the applicant for exemption in writing and make a final decision to grant or refuse the exemption or declare that the agreement does not require an exemption within six months after the submission of complete information. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegu v&otilde;ib Konkurentsiamet pikendada &uuml;ksnes erandi taotleja kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Competition Board may extend the deadlines provided for in subsections (2) and (3) of this section only with the written consent of the applicant for exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandi andmise otsused </eesti>
<inglise>Decision to grant exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud otsus on kirjalik ja sisaldab otsuse p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A decision specified in subsection 11 (1) of this Act shall be in writing and contain justification for the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erandi andmise otsus v&otilde;ib sisaldada kokkuleppepooltele tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi, mille t&auml;itmine on erandi kehtimiseks kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision to grant an exemption may contain conditions or obligations for the parties to the agreement the fulfilment of which is mandatory for the exemption to be valid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib anda erandi kuni viieks aastaks, kusjuures m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;ib erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaega pikendada erandi andmise otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may grant an exemption for up to five years, whereupon the term of the exemption may be extended by a decision to grant an exemption upon expiry of the specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Taotluse erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaja pikendamiseks esitab erandi saanud kokkuleppepool v&otilde;i -pooled kirjalikult v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud enne otsuses toodud erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A party or the parties to an agreement to whom an exemption is granted shall submit an application for extension of the exemption at least six months before expiry of the exemption specified in the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib erandi andmise otsuse t&uuml;histada v&otilde;i seda muuta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may revoke or amend a decision to grant an exemption if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on toimunud olulisi muudatusi nimetatud otsuse aluseks olnud andmetes v&otilde;i tingimustes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) substantial changes take place in the information or conditions which are the basis of the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kokkuleppepool v&otilde;i -pooled rikuvad nimetatud otsusega neile pandud kohustusi v&otilde;i tingimusi v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>2) a party or parties to the agreement violate the obligations or conditions imposed on them by the decision; or </inglise>
<eesti>3) otsus p&otilde;hines mittet&auml;ielikul, eba&otilde;igel v&otilde;i eksitaval teabel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the decision is based on incomplete, incorrect or misleading information. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&otilde;ik k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 1 ja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 5 alusel tehtud otsused avaldatakse Riigi Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) All decisions made pursuant to clause 11 (1) 1) of this Act and subsection (5) of this section are published in the Riigi Teataja. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Kaubaturgu valitsev ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking Dominating Market </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaubaturgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of undertaking dominating market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaubaturgu valitsev ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on ettev&otilde;tja, kellele kuulub kaubaturul v&auml;hemalt 40 protsenti k&auml;ibest v&otilde;i kelle majanduslik positsioon v&otilde;imaldab tal antud kaubaturul tegutseda arvestataval m&auml;&auml;ral s&otilde;ltumatult konkurentidest, varustajatest ja ostjatest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, an undertaking dominating the market is an undertaking which accounts for at least 40 per cent of the turnover in the market or whose economic position enables the undertaking to operate in the market to an appreciable extent independently of competitors, suppliers and buyers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaks v&otilde;i enam &uuml;ksteisega majanduslikult seotud ettev&otilde;tjat on k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses kaubaturgu &uuml;hiselt valitsevad ettev&otilde;tjad, kui nendele koos kuulub kaubaturul v&auml;hemalt 40 protsenti k&auml;ibest v&otilde;i kelle majanduslik positsioon v&otilde;imaldab neil antud kaubaturul tegutseda arvestataval m&auml;&auml;ral s&otilde;ltumatult konkurentidest, varustajatest ja ostjatest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, two or more economically linked undertakings are undertakings which jointly dominate a market if they jointly control at least 40 per cent of the turnover in the market or whose economic position enables them to operate in the market to an appreciable extent independently of competitors, suppliers and buyers. </inglise>
<eesti>Majanduslik side k&auml;esoleva s&auml;tte m&otilde;istes on n&auml;iteks: </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this provision, an economic link is, for example: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tjatevaheline kokkulepe, mis annab selle osalistele arvestatava tehnoloogilise v&otilde;i kaubandusliku eelise teiste ettev&otilde;tjate ees vastaval kaubaturul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an agreement between undertakings which gives an appreciable technological or commercial advantage to the parties thereto compared to other undertakings in the relevant market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tja omab k&uuml;llaldast osa teise ettev&otilde;tja aktsiatest, osadest, h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igustest v&otilde;i kontrolli juhatuse &uuml;le (v&otilde;i nende asjaolude kombinatsioon), mis annab talle v&otilde;imaluse oluliselt m&otilde;jutada teise ettev&otilde;tja otsuseid v&otilde;i majandustegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) an undertaking owns sufficient part of the stocks, shares, votes or control over the management board of another undertaking (or a combination of such circumstances) which enables the undertaking to significantly influence the decisions or economic activities of the other undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kaubaturgu valitsevaks ettev&otilde;tjaks on ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 15 ja 16 nimetatud eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i loomulikku monopoli omavad ettev&otilde;tjad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Undertakings with special or exclusive rights or a natural monopoly specified in &sect;&sect; 15 and 16 of this Act are also undertakings dominating the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaubaturgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja seisundi kuritarvitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Abuse by undertaking of dominant position in market </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on kaubaturgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja seisundi otsene v&otilde;i kaudne kuritarvitamine kaubaturul, s.o. &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme &uuml;hiselt kaubaturul valitsevat seisundit omava ettev&otilde;tja poolt oma positsiooni &auml;rakasutamine konkurentsivabaduse kahjustamiseks, mis seisneb otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt: </eesti>
<inglise>Any direct or indirect abuse by an undertaking of a dominant position within a market, i.e. abuse by one undertaking or several undertakings, which jointly have a dominant position in the market to restrict competition which directly or indirectly consists in: </inglise>
<eesti>1) eba&otilde;iglaste hinnakujundamise tingimuste v&otilde;i muude eba&otilde;iglaste &auml;ritingimuste rakendamises, sealhulgas kaupade p&otilde;hjendamatu m&uuml;&uuml;mine alla omahinna, mis kahjustab teise ettev&otilde;tja tegevust kaubaturul v&otilde;i t&otilde;rjub teda kaubaturult v&auml;lja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) imposing unfair pricing conditions or other unfair trading conditions, including the unjustified sale of goods below the cost price which prejudices the activities of another undertaking in the market or excludes another undertaking from the market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tootmise, teenindamise, kaubaturu, tehnilise arengu v&otilde;i investeeringute piiramises ostjate kahjuks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) limiting production, services, markets, technical development or investments to the prejudice of consumers; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsete kokkulepete s&otilde;lmimisel erinevate tingimuste rakendamises erinevatele ettev&otilde;tjatele, pannes m&otilde;ne neist sellega kas soodsamasse v&otilde;i ebasoodsamasse konkurentsiolukorda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) applying dissimilar conditions upon entry into equivalent agreements with other undertakings, thereby placing some of them at a competitive advantage or disadvantage; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimisel selliste tingimuste seadmises, mille kohaselt &uuml;he kokkuleppe eelduseks on teine, esimesega mitteseotud kokkulepe, mida teine pool vaba valiku korral ei s&otilde;lmiks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) upon entry into agreements making one agreement conditional on another agreement that is unrelated to the first agreement, into which the other party would not enter voluntarily; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettev&otilde;tja sundimises endaga v&otilde;i teise ettev&otilde;tjaga &uuml;hinemiseks v&otilde;i kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimiseks v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) forcing an undertaking to merge with the undertaking or another undertaking or to enter into an agreement or concerted practices; </inglise>
<eesti>6) p&otilde;hjendamatus keeldumises kauba m&uuml;&uuml;misest teisele ettev&otilde;tjale; </eesti>
<inglise>6) unjustified refusal to sell goods to another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>7) m&uuml;&uuml;gi- v&otilde;i ostupakkumistel osalenud ettev&otilde;tjate ebav&otilde;rdses kohtlemises v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>7) unequal treatment of undertakings which participate in sales offers or purchase bids; or </inglise>
<eesti>8) konkurentsivabaduse kahjustamises k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi punktides 1-7 nimetamata viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>8) restricting competition in a manner not specified in clauses 1) -7) of this section, is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igusega ettev&otilde;tja ning loomulik monopol </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking with Special or Exclusive Rights or Natural Monopoly </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust omav ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking with special or exclusive rights </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igusena k&auml;sitatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse poolt ettev&otilde;tjale antud luba, mis v&otilde;imaldab tal olla kaubaturul teiste ettev&otilde;tjatega v&otilde;rreldes eelisseisundis v&otilde;i ainsaks ettev&otilde;tjaks antud kaubaturul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, special or exclusive rights are permission granted to an undertaking by the state or a local government which enables the undertaking to have a competitive advantage in the market over other undertakings or to be the only undertaking in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiasutusel v&otilde;i kohalikul omavalitsusel on &otilde;igus &otilde;igusaktide alusel anda ettev&otilde;tjale eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State agencies and local governments have the right to grant special or exclusive rights to undertakings pursuant to legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse andmise aluseks olev &otilde;igusakt ei s&auml;testa eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse andmise korda, tuleb vastava &otilde;iguse andmiseks korraldada avalik konkurss Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If legislation on the basis of which special or exclusive rights are granted does not provide the procedure for the grant of special or exclusive rights, a public competition for the grant of such rights shall be arranged pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Loomuliku monopoli m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of natural monopoly </inglise>
<eesti>Loomulik monopol on ettev&otilde;tjal, kelle omandis, valduses v&otilde;i opereerimisel on v&otilde;rgustik v&otilde;i infrastruktuur, mida teisel isikul ei ole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i ei ole majanduslikult otstarbekas dubleerida, ja mis annab talle kaubaturul valitseva seisundi. </eesti>
<inglise>An undertaking has a natural monopoly if it owns, possesses or operates a network or infrastructure which other persons cannot duplicate or for whom it is economically inexpedient to duplicate and which gives the undertaking a dominant position in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i loomulikku monopoli omava ettev&otilde;tja tegevuse piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions to activities of undertakings with special or exclusive rights or natural monopoly </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust omavale ettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;ib talle selle &otilde;iguse andnud riigiasutus v&otilde;i kohalik omavalitsus kehtestada hindade reguleerimise korra v&otilde;i kasutatavad hinnad v&otilde;i esitada muid tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi, et nende ettev&otilde;tjate kaupade ostjad v&otilde;i nendele ettev&otilde;tjatele kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;jad ei satuks oluliselt halvemasse olukorda, kui nad oleksid siis, kui antud valdkonnas toimiks vaba konkurents. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The state agency or local government which grants special or exclusive rights to an undertaking may establish the procedure for regulation of prices or the prices to be used or impose other conditions or obligations on the undertaking so that the buyers of goods of such undertaking or sellers of goods to such undertaking are not placed in a substantially worse situation than they would be in if competition were present in that area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Loomulikku monopoli omavale ettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;ib eriseadusega m&auml;&auml;ratud riigiasutus v&otilde;i kohalik omavalitsus v&otilde;i eriseaduse puudumisel Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i kohalik omavalitsus kehtestada hindade reguleerimise korra v&otilde;i kasutatavad hinnad v&otilde;i esitada muid tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi, et nende ettev&otilde;tjate kaupade ostjad v&otilde;i nendele ettev&otilde;tjatele kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;jad ei satuks oluliselt halvemasse olukorda, kui nad oleksid siis, kui antud valdkonnas toimiks vaba konkurents. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State agencies and local governments determined by a specific Act or, in the absence of a specific Act, the Government of the Republic and local governments may establish the procedure for regulation of prices or the prices to be used or impose other conditions or obligations on an undertaking which has a natural monopoly so that the buyers of goods of such undertaking or sellers of goods to such undertaking are not placed in a substantially worse situation than they would be in if competition were present in that area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i loomulikku monopoli omava ettev&otilde;tja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of undertakings with special or exclusive rights or natural monopoly </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i loomulikku monopoli omav ettev&otilde;tja peab: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An undertaking with special or exclusive rights or a natural monopoly shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lubama teisele ettev&otilde;tjale m&otilde;istlikel ja mittediskrimineerivatel tingimustel juurdep&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;rgustikule v&otilde;i infrastruktuurile teenustega varustamise v&otilde;i nende m&uuml;&uuml;gi eesm&auml;rgil; </eesti>
<inglise>1) permit access to the network or infrastructure by other undertakings under reasonable and non-discriminatory conditions for the purpose of provision or sale of services; </inglise>
<eesti>2) hoidma raamatupidamises selget vahet erinevate p&otilde;hi- ja lisategevusalade vahel (n&auml;iteks tootmine, edastamine, turustamine ja ettev&otilde;tja muud tegevusalad), tagades sellega majandusarvestuste l&auml;bipaistvuse, ning avalikustama kulutused tarbijatele ja nende esindajatele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) draw a clear distinction in accounting between primary and secondary activities (for example production, transportation, marketing and other activities of the undertaking) thereby ensuring the transparency of accounting, and disclose all expenses to consumers and their representatives; </inglise>
<eesti>3) eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i loomuliku monopoli teostamiseks vajalikke asju ostma ja ehitust&ouml;id ning teenuseid tellima riigihangete seaduses (RT I 1995, 54, 883; 1997, 9, 79; 1998, 38, 561; 1999, 16, 271; 92, 824; 97, 859) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>3) purchase things and order construction work and services necessary for the exercise of special or exclusive rights or a natural monopoly pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Public Procurement Act (RT I 1995, 54, 883; 1997, 9, 79; 1998, 38, 561; 1999, 16, 271; 92, 824; 97, 859). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i loomulikku monopoli omav ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib keelduda lubamast teistele ettev&otilde;tjatele juurdep&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;rgustikule v&otilde;i infrastruktuurile, kui keeldumiseks on j&auml;rgmised objektiivsed alused: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An undertaking with special or exclusive rights or a natural monopoly may refuse access to the undertaking's network or infrastructure to other undertakings if the refusal is based on the following objective reasons: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on ohustatud antud v&otilde;rgustiku v&otilde;i infrastruktuuriga &uuml;hendatud seadmete ohutus ja turvalisus ning v&otilde;rgustiku v&otilde;i infrastruktuuri t&ouml;&ouml; efektiivsus ja turvalisus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the safety and security of the equipment connected with the network or infrastructure or the efficiency and security of the operation of such network or infrastructure are endangered; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on ohustatud v&otilde;rgustiku v&otilde;i infrastruktuuri terviklikkuse hoidmine v&otilde;i vastastikuses seoses toimimine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) maintenance of the integrity of the network or infrastructure or inter-operability of services is endangered; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seadmed, mida soovitakse &uuml;hendada v&otilde;rgustikku v&otilde;i infrastruktuuri, ei vasta kehtivatele tehnilistele standarditele v&otilde;i reeglitele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) equipment to be connected to the network or infrastructure is not in conformity with established technical standards or rules; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juurdep&auml;&auml;su taotleval ettev&otilde;tjal puuduvad tehnilised ja finantsilised v&otilde;imalused ning vahendid, et vajalikul m&auml;&auml;ral efektiivselt ja turvaliselt teenindada vastava v&otilde;rgustiku v&otilde;i infrastruktuuri kaudu v&otilde;i abil v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>4) the undertaking applying for access lacks the technical and financial capabilities and resources to efficiently and safely, to the necessary extent, provide services through or with the assistance of the network or infrastructure; or </inglise>
<eesti>5) juurdep&auml;&auml;su tagaj&auml;rjel ei ole seadustes s&auml;testatud andmete kaitse tagatud. </eesti>
<inglise>5) as a result of access, data protection provided by law is not ensured. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi </eesti>
<inglise>State Aid </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on riigi, linna v&otilde;i valla poolt v&otilde;i nende vahenditest &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik missugusel kujul antav soodustus, mis moonutab v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib moonutada konkurentsi, soodustades m&otilde;nda ettev&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i mingite kaupade tootmist v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;ki. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, state aid is an advantage granted in any form whatsoever by the state, a city or rural municipality or through their resources which distorts or threatens to distort competition by favouring certain undertakings or the production or sale of certain goods. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks v&otilde;ib olla n&auml;iteks rahaline abi, maksuv&otilde;lgade tasumise ajatamine, v&otilde;lgade kustutamine, laenude andmine oluliselt soodsamatel tingimustel kui tavaliselt teistele ettev&otilde;tjatele ja muud abi vormid. </eesti>
<inglise>Such aid may be, for example, financial aid, postponement of payment of tax arrears, debt write-offs and the grant of loans under essentially more favourable terms than usually given to other undertakings, and other forms of aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiabi, v&auml;lja arvatud abi laevaehitusele, transpordile, p&otilde;llumajandusele ja kalandusele ning ekspordiabi, on k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;istes v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega, kui see ei &uuml;leta ettev&otilde;tja kohta 1,5 miljonit krooni kolme j&auml;rjestikuse aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, state aid, except aid to shipbuilding, transport, agriculture, fisheries and export aid, is of minor importance if it does not exceed 1.5 million kroons per undertaking over three subsequent years. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for grant of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Anda v&otilde;ib ainult &uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobivat riigiabi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Only state aid compatible with the public interest may be granted. (10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following state aid shall be compatible with the public interest: </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobiv riigiabi on: 1) sotsiaalse iseloomuga riigiabi tingimusel, et sellise riigiabi andmisega ei kaasne asjassepuutuvate toodete p&auml;ritoluga seotud diskrimineerimist; 2) riigiabi loodus&otilde;nnetuste ja muude erakorraliste s&uuml;ndmuste t&otilde;ttu tekkinud kahju heastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>1) state aid having a social character provided that such aid is granted without discrimination related to the origin of the products concerned; 2) state aid to make good the damage caused by natural disasters or other exceptional occurrences. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In addition to the provisions of subsection (2) of this section, the following may be consideredto be compatible with the public interest: </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatule v&otilde;ib &uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobivaks pidada: 1) riigiabi majandusliku arengu edendamiseks piirkondades, kus elatustase on ebanormaalselt madal v&otilde;i kus t&ouml;&ouml;puudus on v&auml;ga suur; 2) riigiabi teatud majandustegevuse v&otilde;i teatud majanduspiirkondade arengu soodustamiseks, kui selline abi ei m&otilde;ju majandustingimustele negatiivselt ulatuses, mis on vastuolus &uuml;ldiste huvidega; 3) riigiabi t&otilde;siste majandush&auml;irete k&otilde;rvaldamiseks v&otilde;i 4) riigiabi kultuuri edendamiseks ja kultuurip&auml;randi s&auml;ilitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>1) state aid to promote the economic development of areas where the standard of living is abnormally low or where there is serious unemployment; 2) state aid to facilitate the development of certain economic activity or economic areas where such aid does not adversely affect trading conditions to an extent contrary to the public interest; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. </eesti>
<inglise>3) state aid to remedy a serious disturbance in the economy; or </inglise>
<eesti>01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>state aid to promote culture and heritage conservation. </inglise>

<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud riigiabi: 1) antakse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud perioodiks ja riigiabi andmine l&otilde;petatakse, kui see ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud kriteeriumile; 2) antakse ulatuses, mida on vaja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) State aid specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section: 1) shall be granted for a specified period of time and shall be terminated when it no longer complies with one of the criteria specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>2) shall be granted to the extent needed to achieve an objective specified in subsections (2) or (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud tingimused ei laiene v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega riigiabile. </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) (5) The conditions provided for in subsections (2) and (3) of this section do not extend to state aid of minor importance. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Riigiabi andmise tingimused ja korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The conditions and procedure for the grant of state aid shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi andja v&otilde;ib anda riigiabi, v&auml;lja arvatud valla- ja linnaeelarves etten&auml;htud riigiabi ning v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega riigiabi, ainult rahandusministri eelneval kirjalikul loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A grantor of state aid may grant state aid, except state aid prescribed in a city or rural municipality budget and state aid of minor importance, only with the prior written permission of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusministri k&auml;skkiri, millega luba antakse, avaldatakse ametlikus v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>The directive of the Minister of Finance by which permission is granted shall be published in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja nende liikmesriikide ning Eesti Vabariigi vahelise assotsieerumislepingu (Euroopa lepingu) (RT II 1995, 22-27, 120) artikli 63 l&otilde;ikes 5 etten&auml;htud toodete tootmise, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ja turustamisega tegelevale ettev&otilde;tjale riigiabina antavale rahalisele abile ei kohaldata k&auml;esolevas peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) The provisions of this Chapter do not apply to financial aid granted as state aid to undertakings engaged in the production, processing and marketing of products prescribed in Article 63 (5) of the Europe Agreement establishing an association between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and the Republic of Estonia, of the other part (RT II 1995, 22-27, 120). </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud rahalise abi andmine s&auml;testatakse teiste seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>The grant of such financial aid shall be provided for by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud riigiabi andmise loa taotlus esitatakse rahandusministrile koos kogu vajaliku teabega vastavalt rahandusministri poolt kehtestatavale juhendile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for permission to grant state aid specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be submitted to the Minister of Finance with the necessary information pursuant to the instructions established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhul kui taotluses esitatav teave on mittet&auml;ielik v&otilde;i sisaldab eba&otilde;iget v&otilde;i eksitavat teavet, informeerib rahandusminister taotlejat sellest kirjalikult, n&otilde;udes kogu teabe esitamist ja m&auml;&auml;rates t&auml;htaja selle esitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the information submitted in an application is incomplete or contains incorrect or misleading information, the Minister of Finance shall notify the applicant thereof in writing, demand submission of all information and determine a deadline for submission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul algavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 23 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajad kuup&auml;evast, mil rahandusministrile esitatakse kogu teave. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the terms provided for in subsections 23 (2) and (3) of this Act commence from the date that all information is submitted to the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus teatab rahandusministrile kirjalikult valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarve projektis etten&auml;htud riigiabist, v&auml;lja arvatud v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega riigiabist, enne eelarveprojekti &uuml;leandmist volikogule. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A rural municipality or city government shall notify the Minister of Finance in writing of state aid prescribed in the draft budget of the rural municipality or city, except state aid of minor importance, before the draft budget is presented to the council. </inglise>
<eesti>Teatise vormi kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of the notice shall be established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusministri ning linna- ja vallavalitsuste kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of Minister of Finance and city and rural municipality governments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister k&auml;sitab oma k&otilde;ikide riigiabi puudutavate otsuste puhul, &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik kas seda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 20 ja 21 alusel lubatakse v&otilde;i mitte, vastaval tegevusalal tegutsevaid k&otilde;iki ettev&otilde;tjaid ning nende kaupu &uuml;hetaoliselt ja erapooletult, v&otilde;ttes arvesse k&otilde;iki asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance shall apply uniform and impartial treatment to all undertakings in the market and their goods taking into account all circumstances upon making decisions concerning state aid regardless of whether the grant of state aid is allowed or not on the basis of &sect;&sect; 20 and 21 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister rakendab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 20 toodud kriteeriume k&otilde;igis oma otsustes, mis puudutavad riigiabi andmise lubamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance shall apply all the criteria specified in &sect; 20 of this Act in all his or her decisions concerning permission to grant state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla- ja linnavalitsustel on keelatud eelarveprojektis ette n&auml;ha riigiabi, mis ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 20. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Rural municipality and city governments are prohibited to prescribe state aid which does not comply with &sect; 20 of this Act in a draft budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahandusminister j&auml;lgib linna- v&otilde;i vallaeelarvetes sisalduva riigiabi andmist ja kasutamist, v&auml;lja arvatud v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega riigiabi, ning teeb vajadusel ettepaneku v&otilde;tta tarvitusele abin&otilde;ud, mis kindlustaksid riigiabi vastavuse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 20. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Finance monitors the grant and use of state aid set out in city and rural municipality budgets, except state aid of minor importance, and shall, if necessary, make a proposal to employ measures to ensure the compliance of state aid with &sect; 20 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmise luba </eesti>
<inglise>Permission to grant state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister teeb loataotluse kohta &uuml;he j&auml;rgnevatest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance shall make one of the following decisions concerning an application for state aid: </inglise>
<eesti>1) annab loa, kui ta leiab, et taotlus vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to grant permission if he or she finds that the application complies with the provisions of &sect; 20 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) keeldub loa andmisest, kui ta leiab, et taotlus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to refuse permission if he or she finds that the application does not comply with the provisions of &sect; 20 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) alustab loataotluse suhtes t&auml;iendava menetluse, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks oleva kokkuleppe sobivus loa saamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 kriteeriumide alusel on kaheldav ning otsuse langetamiseks loa andmise v&otilde;i sellest keeldumise kohta on vaja saada t&auml;iendavat teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to initiate supplementary proceedings concerning the application for state aid if he or she finds that it is doubtful whether the agreement which is the basis for the grant of permission pursuant to &sect; 20 of this Act qualifies for state aid, and it is necessary to obtain additional information in order to decide to grant or refuse permission. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister teeb otsuse riigiabi andmise loataotluse kohta kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi vajalike andmete esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance shall make a decision concerning an application for the grant of state aid within two months after submission of all necessary information. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui rahandusminister otsustab algatada t&auml;iendava menetluse riigiabi andmise loataotluse kohta, teatab ta sellest kirjalikult taotlejale ning teeb l&otilde;pliku otsuse riigiabi andmise kohta kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast kogu teabe saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the Minister of Finance decides to commence further proceedings concerning an application for the grant of state aid, he or she shall notify the applicant thereof in writing and make a final decision concerning the grant of state aid within six months after receipt of all information. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 alusel t&auml;iendava menetluse teostamisel v&otilde;tab rahandusminister arvesse planeeritava riigiabi andja ja saaja ning teiste poolte k&otilde;iki kirjalikke ja suulisi seletusi, kellel on p&otilde;hjendatud huvi antud k&uuml;simuse vastu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In conducting further proceedings on the basis of subsection (3) of this section, the Minister of Finance shall take into account all written and oral explanations given by the planned grantor and beneficiary of state aid and other parties with a legitimate interest in the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui rahandusminister ei tee otsust k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, loetakse riigiabi lubatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the Minister of Finance does not make a decision within the term provided for in this section, permission for the grant of state aid is deemed to be granted. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Riigiabi andmise luba v&otilde;ib sisaldada riigiabi saajale tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi, mille t&auml;itmine on selle abi kasutamise puhul kohustuslik. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A decision to grant state aid may contain conditions and obligations for the beneficiary of state aid the fulfilment of which is mandatory upon the use of state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib enda tehtud riigiabi andmise loa t&uuml;histada v&otilde;i seda muuta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Minister of Finance may revoke or amend his or her permission to grant state aid if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on toimunud olulisi muudatusi nimetatud loa aluseks olnud teabes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) substantial changes take place in the information which is the basis of such permission; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tja rikub nimetatud loaga talle pandud tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>2) an undertaking violates the conditions or obligations imposed on it; or </inglise>
<eesti>3) luba p&otilde;hines mittet&auml;ielikul, eba&otilde;igel v&otilde;i eksitaval teabel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the permission is based on incomplete, incorrect or misleading information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi tagasimaksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Repayment of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda riigiabi saajalt riigiabi tagasimaksmist riigieelarve tuludesse, riigiabi andmise otsuse t&uuml;histamist v&otilde;i riigiabi andmise peatamist, kui: 1) riigiabist ei ole rahandusministrile vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 21 teatatud; 2) riigiabi kasutatakse eesm&auml;rgil, mis on erinev kasutusest v&otilde;i eesm&auml;rgist, mis oli toodud riigiabi kohta esitatud teabes; 3) ei t&auml;ideta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 23 l&otilde;ike 6 alusel kehtestatud tingimust v&otilde;i kohustust v&otilde;i 4) riigiabi andmise otsus p&otilde;hines riigiabi saaja esitatud mittet&auml;ielikul, eba&otilde;igel v&otilde;i eksitaval teabel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance may require from a beneficiary of state aid the repayment of state aid to the revenue of state budget, the revocation of permission to grant state aid or suspension of the grant of state aid if: 1) the Minister of Finance is not notified of the state aid pursuant to &sect; 21 of this Act; </inglise>

<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a condition or obligation established pursuant to subsection 23 (6) of this Act is not fulfilled; or </inglise>
<eesti>01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>4) the decision to grant state aid is based on incomplete, incorrect or misleading information submitted by the beneficiary of state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda p&otilde;hjendatud m&auml;&auml;raga intressi iga riigiabi tagasimaksmise juhtumi korral k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel tagasimakstava riigiabi summalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) (2) The Minister of Finance has the right to demand a justified interest rate on the amount of repaid state aid in all cases where state aid is repaid pursuant to subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Sissen&otilde;utud intressi summad kantakse riigieelarve tuludesse. </eesti>
<inglise>The collected sums of interest shall be transferred to the revenue of state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hjendatud m&auml;&auml;raga intressiks loetakse riigiabi andmisele v&otilde;i abi lubamise otsusele eelnenud kuu Eesti pankade kroonilaenude keskmist intressim&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>Justified interest rate is the average interest rate of loans in kroons of Estonian banks of the month preceding the grant of state aid or the decision granting permission to grant state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>Intressi arvestatakse riigiabi k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>Interest shall be calculated from the moment when state aid is made available. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi aruandlus </eesti>
<inglise>Reporting on state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi andja, see on edastaja, laenu tagaja, maksu ajataja jne, esitab kord aastas rahandusministri kehtestatud kuup&auml;evaks ja vormis aruande riigiabi andmise ja kasutamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Grantors of state aid, that is distributors, guarantors of loans, tax administrators, etc., shall submit a report on the grant and use of state aid once a year by the date and in the form established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruanne esitatakse ka valla- ja linnaeelarves sisalduva riigiabi ning v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega riigiabi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Reports shall also be submitted concerning state aid set out in the city and rural municipality budgets and state aid of minor importance. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister koostab 12 kuu jooksul, alates kalendriaasta l&otilde;ppemisest, aruande kogu sellel aastal antud riigiabi kohta, mis esitatakse kinnitamiseks Vabariigi Valitsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance shall prepare a report within twelve months after the end of a calendar year on all state aid granted during that year which shall be submitted to the Government of the Republic for approval. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.11.1999 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.11.99 entered into force 01.01.00 - RT I 1999, 89, 813) </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemise kontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Merger Control </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemine </eesti>
<inglise>Merger </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemisena k&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;ttes k&auml;sitatakse ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;hinemist &auml;riseadustiku (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91/93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303) t&auml;henduses, samuti muul viisil &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tja poolt valitseva m&otilde;ju saavutamist teise ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, a merger is deemed to arise where undertakings merge as defined in the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91/93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303) or where an undertaking acquires control over another undertaking by some other means. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hinemisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of merger </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;hinemisest tuleb eelnevalt Konkurentsiametile teatada, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board shall be notified of a merger in advance if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hinevate poolte aastane k&auml;ive kokku &uuml;letab 100 miljonit krooni v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) the aggregate annual turnover of the merging parties exceeds 100 million kroons; or </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;hinevad pooled eraldi v&otilde;i koos omavad kontrolli v&auml;hemalt 40 protsendi &uuml;le kaubaturust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the merging parties separately or jointly have control over more than 40 per cent of the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiametile esitatakse &uuml;hinemisteade koos &uuml;hinemislepingu, &uuml;hinemisaruande ja &uuml;hinemisotsusega nende olemasolu korral vastavalt kas &auml;riseadustikule, mittetulundus&uuml;hingute seadusele (RT I 1996, 42, 811; 1998, 96, 1515; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 67, 658) v&otilde;i sihtasutuste seadusele (RT I 1995, 92, 1604; 1996, 42, 811; 1998, 36/37, 552; 59, 941; 1999, 10, 155) ning muu vajaliku teabega vastavalt rahandusministri poolt kehtestatavale juhendile, kusjuures Konkurentsiameti n&otilde;udmisel peab esitama tutvumiseks dokumentide originaalid v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema esindaja poolt t&otilde;estatud &auml;rakirjad. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A merger notice shall be submitted to the Competition Board together with the merger agreement, merger report and merger decision, if these exist, in accordance with the Commercial Code, the Non-profit Associations Act (RT 1 1996, 42, 811; 1998, 96, 1515; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 67, 658) or the Foundations Act (RT 1 1995, 92, 1604; 1996, 42, 811; 1998, 36/37, 552; 59, 941; 1999, 10, 155), and other necessary information pursuant to the instructions established by the Minister of Finance, whereupon, at the request of the Competition Board, the documents shall be submitted as originals or copies certified by the undertaking or its representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui &uuml;hinemisteates v&otilde;i selle lisades sisalduv teave on mittet&auml;ielik, eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i eksitav, teatab Konkurentsiamet sellest teatajale kirjalikult, n&otilde;udes kogu teabe esitamist ja m&auml;&auml;rates selle esitamiseks t&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If information contained in a merger notice or its annexes is incomplete, incorrect or misleading, the Competition Board shall notify the notifying party thereof in writing and shall demand the provision of all information and determine a deadline for provision thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;hinemist ei v&otilde;i l&auml;bi viia enne &uuml;he kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumist p&auml;rast kogu teabe esitamist Konkurentsiametile, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui Konkurentsiametiga lepitakse kirjalikult kokku teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A merger may not be implemented earlier than within one month after the submission of all information to the Competition Board unless otherwise agreed with the Competition Board in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teabe juurde, mida &uuml;hinemisest teataja peab &auml;risaladuseks, teeb ta vastava m&auml;rke v&otilde;i annab selle teabe eraldi lisana. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The notifying party shall designate information he or she deems to be a business secret or shall submit such information separately as an annex. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;lvatu konkurents </eesti>
<inglise>Unfair Competition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;lvatu konkurentsi keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on unfair competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&otilde;lvatuks konkurentsiks on vaba ettev&otilde;tlust kahjustavad heade kommete ja tavadega vastuolus olevad teod, sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unfair competition means any act which restricts free enterprise and is contrary to good morals and customs, including: </inglise>
<eesti>1) eksitava teabe avaldamine, avaldamiseks esitamine v&otilde;i tellimine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the publication of misleading information, or presentation or ordering of misleading information for publication; </inglise>
<eesti>2) konkurendi v&otilde;i tema kauba halvustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the disparagement of a competitor or a competitor's goods; </inglise>
<eesti>3) konfidentsiaalse teabe kuritarvitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the misuse of confidential information; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teise ettev&otilde;tja t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i esindaja &auml;rakasutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the misuse of an employee or representative of another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;gi k&otilde;lvatu piiramine v&otilde;i soodustamine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) unfair restriction or promotion of the sale of goods. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&otilde;lvatu konkurents on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unfair competition is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reklaamina k&auml;sitletava eksitava, k&otilde;lvatu v&otilde;i halvustava teabe puhul rakendatakse reklaamiseaduse (RT I 1997, 52, 835; 1999, 27, 388; 30, 415) s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of the Advertising Act (RT 1 1997, 52, 835; 1999, 27, 388; 30, 415) apply to misleading, offensive or denigratory information as a method of advertising. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Eksitava teabe avaldamiseks esitamine v&otilde;i tellimine </eesti>
<inglise>Presentation or ordering of misleading information for publication </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eksitav teave on ebat&otilde;este andmete avaldamine v&otilde;i avaldamiseks esitamine v&otilde;i tellimine kas enda v&otilde;i teise samal kaubaturul osaleva ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i nende kauba kohta, mis v&otilde;ivad ostja tavalise t&auml;helepanelikkuse juures tekitada pakkumisest eksliku mulje. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Misleading information means the publication, or presentation or ordering of false information for publication either concerning oneself or another undertaking which is a participant in the same market or the undertaking's goods which may leave a misleading impression of an offer, given ordinary attention by the buyer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud andmete all m&otilde;istetakse eelk&otilde;ige teavet pakutavate kaupade p&auml;ritolu, omaduste, valmistamisviisi, hankimisviisi v&otilde;i -allikate, hinna, tariifi, allahindluse, auhindamise, m&uuml;&uuml;gi p&otilde;hjuste ja varude suuruse ning ettev&otilde;tja ees&otilde;iguste, finantsseisundi ja muude omaduste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information specified in subsection (1) of this section primarily refers to information concerning the origin, qualities, method of production, means or sources of supply, price, tariff, discounts, prizes awarded, reasons for sale and the amount of stock of the goods offered, as well as preferential rights, financial status and other qualities of the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kauba tootja, selle p&auml;ritolu ja muude omaduste m&auml;rkimine on eksitav ka juhul, kui kaubal endal, selle pakendil, saatedokumentides v&otilde;i mujal on kasutatud m&auml;rki, teavet, tunnust v&otilde;i nimetust, mis tavalise t&auml;helepanelikkuse juures v&otilde;ib viia eksitusele kauba valmistamise koha, tootja v&otilde;i kauba omaduste suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Markings concerning the producer, origin or other qualities of goods are also misleading if a mark, information, description or a name is used on the goods, its packaging or accompanying documents or elsewhere which may be misleading as regards the place of production, the producer or the qualities of the goods, given ordinary attention by the buyer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurendi v&otilde;i tema kauba halvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disparagement of competitor or its goods </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurendi v&otilde;i tema kauba halvustamine on valeteadete levitamine samal kaubaturul tegutseva teise ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema poolt m&uuml;&uuml;dava kauba kohta, millega kahjustatakse v&otilde;i v&otilde;idakse kahjustada teise ettev&otilde;tja mainet v&otilde;i tema majandustegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>Disparagement of a competitor or its goods means the dissemination of false information concerning another undertaking or goods sold by another undertaking in the same market which harms or may harm the reputation or economic activities of the other undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Konfidentsiaalse teabe kuritarvitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Misuse of confidential information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konfidentsiaalne teave on ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;sutuses olev tehniline, tehnoloogiline v&otilde;i muu &auml;rialane teave, mille avaldamine ei ole kohustuslik, samuti andmed kaubanduslike l&auml;bir&auml;&auml;kimiste, tehingute, turu-uuringute ja muude asjaolude kohta: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Confidential information means any technical, technological or other business information the publication of which is not mandatory, and information concerning commercial negotiations, transactions, market research and other circumstances: </inglise>
<eesti>1) mida avaldatakse teistele isikutele ainult konfidentsiaalselt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) which is disclosed to other persons only on a confidential basis; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mille saladuses hoidmist peab see ettev&otilde;tja p&otilde;hjendatult vajalikuks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the confidentiality of which the undertaking considers necessary for a justified reason; </inglise>
<eesti>3) mis ei ole ostjatele v&otilde;i potentsiaalsetele ostjatele selle ettev&otilde;tja kohta &uuml;ldiselt k&auml;ttesaadav v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>3) which is not generally available to buyers or potential buyers concerning such undertaking; or </inglise>
<eesti>4) mis ei ole k&auml;ttesaadav vastaval kaubaturul tegutseva ettev&otilde;tja poolt v&otilde;i tema nimel teostatava j&auml;relep&auml;rimise abil. </eesti>
<inglise>4) which is not available on the basis of an inquiry by or in the name of an undertaking operating in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konfidentsiaalse teabe kuritarvitamine on teise ettev&otilde;tja konfidentsiaalse teabe kasutamine, kui vastavad andmed on saadud seadusevastaselt v&otilde;i nende kasutamine on vastuolus teise ettev&otilde;tjaga s&otilde;lmitud kokkuleppega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Misuse of confidential information means the use of confidential information of another undertaking if such information is obtained unlawfully or the use thereof is contrary to an agreement entered into with the other undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise ettev&otilde;tja t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i esindaja &auml;rakasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Misuse of employee or representative of another undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>Teise ettev&otilde;tja t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i esindaja &auml;rakasutamine on tema m&otilde;jutamine tegutsema m&otilde;jutaja v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku huvides konkurentsieeliste saamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Misuse of an employee or representative of another undertaking means influencing him or her to act in the interests of the influencing party or a third person in order to achieve a competitive advantage. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;gi k&otilde;lvatu piiramine v&otilde;i soodustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Unfair restriction or promotion of sale of goods </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;gi k&otilde;lvatu piiramine on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unfair restriction of the sale of goods means: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ostjale m&uuml;&uuml;davate kaupade koguse v&otilde;i teenuste hulga piiramine v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;gi sidumine mingite tingimustega, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui see on kauba kasutamiseks tingimata vajalik v&otilde;i on seotud sooduspakkumisega v&otilde;i tuleneb &otilde;igusaktidest, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) restriction of the amount of goods or services to be sold to a buyer or subjecting such sale to any condition unless this is absolutely necessary for using such good or is related to a special offer or arises from legislation; or </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;leskutse m&uuml;&uuml;gi- v&otilde;i ostukeelu rakendamiseks teise ettev&otilde;tja suhtes, kes tegutseb samal kaubaturul. </eesti>
<inglise>2) calling for implementation of a prohibition on sale or purchase against some other undertaking operating in the same market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;gi k&otilde;lvatu soodustamine on nende m&uuml;&uuml;gi sidumine kohustusega osta teisi kaupu v&otilde;i leida uus ostja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unfair promotion of the sale of goods means subjecting the sale thereof to the obligation to purchase other goods or to find a new buyer. </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsi riikliku j&auml;relevalve asutused </eesti>
<inglise>State competition supervisory authorities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmise &uuml;le, v&auml;lja arvatud krediidiasutuste ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberivahendajate osas, teostab j&auml;relevalvet Konkurentsiamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board supervises the implementation of this Act, except in respect of credit institutions and securities brokers. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.08.2000 - RT I 2000, 53, 343) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.00 entered into force 01.08.00 - RT I 2000, 53, 343) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet krediidiasutuste ja v&auml;&auml;rtpaberivahendajate konkurentsi &uuml;le teostab vastava ala riikliku j&auml;relevalve asutus, kusjuures Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus avaldada soovitusliku iseloomuga seisukohti ja kontrollida k&otilde;iki &uuml;hinemisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) State supervision over the competition of credit institutions and securities brokers is exercised by the state supervision authority in the relevant field whereupon the Competition Board has the right to present opinions as recommendations and exercise control over all mergers. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2000 j&otilde;ust. 01.08.2000 - RT I 2000, 53, 343) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.00 entered into force 01.08.00 - RT I 2000, 53, 343) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seadusega Konkurentsiametile konkurentsi riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks antud &otilde;igused ja kohustused laienevad ka k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud riikliku j&auml;relevalve asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rights and obligations of the Competition Board under this Act to exercise state supervision over competition also extend to the state supervision authorities specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of Competition Board </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiamet on p&auml;dev teostama k&otilde;iki k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel temale pandud toiminguid ja v&otilde;tma tarvitusele meetmeid konkurentsivabaduse kaitsmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board is competent to perform all acts assigned to it by this Act and to take measures to protect competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiamet anal&uuml;&uuml;sib konkurentsi olukorda, kavandab konkurentsivabadust soodustavaid meetmeid, annab soovitusi konkurentsi olukorra parandamiseks ja teeb ettepanekuid &otilde;igusaktide vastuv&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i muutmiseks ning arendab koost&ouml;&ouml;d teiste riikide ja riikide &uuml;henduste konkurentsialase j&auml;relevalve asutustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Competition Board analyses the competitive situation, designs measures to promote competition, makes recommendations to improve the competitive situation, makes proposals to pass or amend legislation and develops co-operation with competition supervisory authorities of other states and associations of states. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda teavet </eesti>
<inglise>Right of Competition Board to demand information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda ettev&otilde;tjalt, riigiasutuselt ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuselt ning f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt isikult teavet: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board has the right to demand information from undertakings, state agencies, local government agencies and natural persons in order to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) konkurentsi olukorra ja kaubaturu kontrollimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) monitor the situation of competition and markets; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kokkuleppe v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse menetlemisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) conduct proceedings concerning agreements and concerted practices; </inglise>
<eesti>3) erandi andmise otsustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) grant exemptions; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaubaturul valitsevat seisundit omava ettev&otilde;tja tegevuse kontrollimisel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) monitor the activities of undertakings dominating the market; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &uuml;hinemise kontrollimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) monitor mergers; </inglise>
<eesti>6) k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise v&otilde;i v&otilde;imaliku rikkumise asja menetlemisel; </eesti>
<inglise>6) conduct proceedings concerning violations or possible violations of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muu j&auml;relevalve teostamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>7) exercise other supervision over implementation of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teavet n&otilde;utakse kirjalikult t&auml;htajaga mitte v&auml;hem kui k&uuml;mme kalendrip&auml;eva, kusjuures nimetatakse &auml;ra taotluse eesm&auml;rk ja juriidiline alus ning viidatakse sanktsioonidele mittet&auml;ieliku, eba&otilde;ige v&otilde;i eksitava teabe esitamise eest ja teabe mitteesitamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The information specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be demanded in writing with a deadline for submission of not less than ten calendar days, whereupon the purpose and legal basis of the request shall be specified and the sanctions provided for the provision of incomplete, incorrect or misleading information or failure to provide information shall be referred to. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud isikutelt v&otilde;i nende esindajatelt v&otilde;tta suulisi seletusi ja koostada selle kohta kokkuv&otilde;te, mis allkirjastatakse koostaja ja seletuse andja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Competition Board has the right to take oral explanations from the persons specified in subsection (1) of this section or their representatives and to prepare a report to be signed by the person preparing the report and the person giving the explanations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda materjale </eesti>
<inglise>Right of Competition Board to demand documentation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus konkurentsi j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks n&otilde;uda k&otilde;igilt ettev&otilde;tjatelt, riigiasutustelt ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutustelt ning f&uuml;&uuml;silistelt isikutelt konkurentsi j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalike dokumentide, nende projektide ja muude materjalide originaale v&otilde;i nende koopiaid v&otilde;i &auml;rakirju, mille originaalilevastavust kinnitab nende esitaja oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to exercise supervision over competition, the Competition Board has the right to demand from undertakings, state agencies, local government agencies and natural persons the originals, copies or transcripts of the documents, drafts thereof and other materials necessary for exercising supervision over competition, the authenticity of which shall be certified by the signature of the person submitting such materials. </inglise>
<eesti>Koopia v&otilde;i &auml;rakirja esitamisel on Konkurentsiametil &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda algdokumenti koopia v&otilde;i &auml;rakirja &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon submission of a copy or transcript, the Competition Board has the right to request the original document to check the correctness of the copy or transcript. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Materjali &uuml;le andnud isiku n&otilde;udel v&auml;ljastatakse talle Konkurentsiameti kinnitus vastava materjali vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of the person who submits the material, the Competition Board shall issue a letter of confirmation to the person concerning receipt of the material. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikul on &otilde;igus Konkurentsiametilt p&auml;rast j&auml;relevalvetoimingute l&otilde;ppu tema poolt esitatud dokumentide, projektide ja muude materjalide originaalid tagasi saada. </eesti>
<inglise>The person has the right to have the originals of the documents, drafts and other materials submitted by him or her returned by the Competition Board after the supervisory proceedings are completed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tja asukoha ja ettev&otilde;tte tegutsemiskoha kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Inspection of seat of undertaking or place of business of undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja k&auml;skkirjaga volitatud Konkurentsiameti ametnikul v&otilde;i esindajal on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise v&otilde;i v&otilde;imaliku rikkumise tuvastamise eesm&auml;rgil kontrollida ettev&otilde;tja asukohta ja ettev&otilde;tte tegutsemiskohta - territooriumi, hoonet, ruumi ja transpordivahendit - ilma eelneva hoiatuseta v&otilde;i eriloata nii t&ouml;&ouml;ajal kui tegutsemiskoha kasutamise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official or representative of the Competition Board authorised by a directive of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy has the right, without prior warning or special permission, to inspect the seat or location of the activities, that is, the territory, buildings, rooms and transport vehicles of the undertaking both during working hours and at any time the location of the activities is used in order to establish any violation or possible violation of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tja n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;ib tema asukohta v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte tegutsemiskohta kontrollida ka muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>The seat of an undertaking or the location of the activities of an undertaking may also be inspected at any other time with the consent of such undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja asukohas v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte tegutsemiskohas esitab kontrolli teostav isik ettev&otilde;tjale, tema esindajale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&auml;ljav&otilde;tte Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja k&auml;skkirjast menetluse alustamise ja kontrolli teostava isiku volitamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the seat of the undertaking or the location of the activities of an undertaking under inspection, the person conducting such inspection shall present to the undertaking, its representative or employee an extract of the directive issued by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy concerning the commencement of the proceedings and authorisation of the person conducting the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiameti ametnikul v&otilde;i esindajal on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kontrollimise teostamisel j&auml;rgmised &otilde;igused ja kohustused: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon an inspection provided for in subsection (1) of this section, an official or representative of the Competition Board has the following rights and obligations: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;igus kontrollida koheselt ettev&otilde;tja tegevust puudutavaid dokumente, nende projekte ja muid materjale ning saada neist kontrollitava kulul originaale v&otilde;i nende koopiaid v&otilde;i &auml;rakirju, mille originaalilevastavust kinnitab nende esitaja oma allkirjaga; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the right to immediately examine documents relating to the activities of the undertaking, drafts thereof and other materials, and to obtain, at the expense of the person under inspection, originals or copies or transcripts thereof, the authenticity of which shall be certified by the signature of the person submitting them; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta ettev&otilde;tjalt, tema esindajalt v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt suulisi seletusi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the right to receive oral explanations from the undertaking, its representatives or employees; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kohustus koostada kontrollimise tulemuste kohta kokkuv&otilde;te kahes eksemplaris, millele v&otilde;etakse kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja allkiri ja millest teine eksemplar antakse alla kirjutanud isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the obligation to prepare a summary of the inspection in two original copies which shall be signed by the undertaking under inspection, its representative or employee and of which a copy shall be given to the signatory. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kontrollimine toimub ettev&otilde;tja, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja teadmisel ning neil on &otilde;igus viibida kontrollimise juures. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The inspection provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be conducted with the knowledge of the undertaking, its representative or employee, and they have the right to be present at the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumi menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings of matter </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul kaebuse v&otilde;i avalduse laekumisest v&otilde;imaliku seaduserikkumise kohta: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall, within ten calendar days after receipt of a complaint or application concerning a possible violation of law, decide: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhtumi menetlemise alustamise otsuse ja m&auml;&auml;rab menetlust l&auml;bi viiva ametniku; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to commence proceedings of the matter and appoint an official to conduct the proceedings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhtumi menetlemise alustamisest keeldumise otsuse, kui esitatud kaebuse v&otilde;i avalduse materjalidest ilmneb, et antud juhtumi menetlemine ei kuulu Konkurentsiameti p&auml;devusse v&otilde;i on ilmne, et tegemist ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumisega. </eesti>
<inglise>2) to refuse to commence proceedings of the matter if it becomes evident from the materials of the complaint or application that the proceedings of the matter are not within the competence of the Competition Board or that this Act has not been violated. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiameti peadirektoril v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itjal on &otilde;igus alustada juhtumi menetlemine omal initsiatiivil konkurentsi olukorra anal&uuml;&uuml;simiseks m&otilde;nel kaubaturul, kaubaturu piiritlemiseks v&otilde;i muu k&auml;esolevast seadusest tuleneva Konkurentsiameti p&auml;devusse kuuluva &uuml;lesande t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy has the right to commence proceedings of a matter on his or her own initiative to analyse the competitive situation in a market, define a market or perform other duties arising from this Act within the competence of the Competition Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiamet avaldab teate juhtumi menetlemise alustamise otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes &uuml;leriigilise levikuga p&auml;evalehes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Competition Board shall publish a notice concerning the decision to initiate proceedings of a matter in at least one daily national newspaper. </inglise>
<eesti>Asjast huvitatud kolmandatel isikutel v&otilde;i nende esindajatel on &otilde;igus esitada oma kirjalik seisukoht juhtumi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Third parties with an interest in the matter or their representatives have the right to present their written opinion concerning the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda asjast huvitatud kolmandatelt isikutelt t&auml;iendavat teavet v&otilde;i kutsuda neid k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud juhtumi suulisele arutelule. </eesti>
<inglise>The Competition Board has the right to demand additional information from third parties with an interest in the matter or to invite them to the oral discussion of the matter provided for in subsection (5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Menetlemise subjektiks olevale ettev&otilde;tjale kirjeldatakse kirjalikus teates selle eesm&auml;rki v&otilde;i oletatavat seaduserikkumist ning n&auml;hakse ette mitte v&auml;hem kui seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva pikkune t&auml;htaeg kirjalike seisukohtade ja materjalide esitamiseks, samuti lisatakse koopiad v&otilde;i &auml;rakirjad teabe aluseks olevast materjalist (selle olemasolu korral) ning viidatakse vastutusele k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The aim of the proceedings or the alleged violation of law shall be described to the undertaking under inspection in a written notice and a term of not less than seven calendar days shall be prescribed for submission of written opinions and materials; copies or transcripts of materials (if they exist) which are the basis of the information shall be appended thereto and a reference shall be made to the liability pursuant to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vajadusel v&otilde;idakse l&auml;bi viia juhtumi suuline arutamine Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja poolt etten&auml;htud p&auml;eval ja kohas, millest teavitatakse ettev&otilde;tjat kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If necessary, the oral discussion of a matter may be conducted on a date and in a place prescribed by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy, of which the undertaking shall be notified in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlemise subjektiks oleva ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel on Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja kohustatud l&auml;bi viima juhtumi suulise arutamise &uuml;hel korral. </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of the undertaking under inspection, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy is required to conduct the oral discussion of the matter in one session. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Juhtumi suulisel arutamisel v&otilde;ivad osaleda ettev&otilde;tjad, nende esindajad, Konkurentsiameti ametnikud, Konkurentsiameti esindajad ning ettev&otilde;tjate ja Konkurentsiameti kokkuleppel kutsutud isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The undertakings, their representatives, officials of the Competition Board, representatives of the Competition Board and persons invited by agreement of the undertakings and the Competition Board may participate in the oral discussion of a matter. </inglise>
<eesti>Arutelu kohta koostatakse kokkuv&otilde;te, millele osav&otilde;tjad alla kirjutavad. </eesti>
<inglise>A summary shall be prepared of the discussion, which shall be signed by the participants. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja poolt kirjalike seisukohtade ja materjalide esitamiseks kehtestatav t&auml;htaeg ei tohi olla l&uuml;hem kui k&uuml;mme kalendrip&auml;eva, samuti tuleb juhtumi suulisest arutamisest ette teatada mitte v&auml;hem kui k&uuml;mme kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The term for submission of written opinions and materials established by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall not be less than ten calendar days, and notice of the oral discussion of a matter shall be given not less than ten calendar days in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema esindaja p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel on Konkurentsiameti peadirektoril v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itjal &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaegu muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>At the reasoned request of an undertaking or its representative, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy has the right to change a determined term. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumi menetlemise l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of proceedings of matter </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb l&otilde;pliku otsuse juhtumi kohta kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast kogu teabe saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make a final decision concerning a matter within three months after receipt of all information. </inglise>
<eesti>Kogu teabe saamisest teavitatakse menetlemise subjektiks olevat ettev&otilde;tjat kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>The undertaking under inspection shall be notified of the receipt of all information in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne &otilde;iguserikkumise tuvastamise otsuse tegemist teavitatakse sellest vastavat ettev&otilde;tjat kirjalikult ja antakse t&auml;htaeg mitte v&auml;hem kui k&uuml;mme p&auml;eva, mille jooksul ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib tutvuda k&otilde;igi materjalidega, v&auml;lja arvatud teise ettev&otilde;tja &auml;risaladus, ning esitada oma seisukoha. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Before making a decision to establish a violation, the undertaking shall be notified thereof in writing and a term of not less than ten days shall be determined during which the undertaking may examine all materials, except the business secrets of other undertakings, and present its position. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhtumi menetlemine l&otilde;petatakse Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Proceedings of a matter shall be terminated by a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy on: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;iguserikkumise mittetuvastamise kohta v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) non-establishment of an offence or: </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;iguserikkumise tuvastamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>2) establishment of an offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud otsus sisaldab p&otilde;hjendust ja vajadusel soovitusi ning otsus antakse ettev&otilde;tjale k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A decision specified in subsection (3) of this section shall contain a justification and, if necessary, recommendations, and the decision shall be given to the undertaking against a signature or shall be mailed to it by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 punktis 2 nimetatud otsus v&otilde;ib sisaldada ettev&otilde;tjale kohustuslikku ettekirjutust v&otilde;i ettepanekut riigiasutustele v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A decision specified in clause (3) 2) of this section may contain a mandatory precept for the undertaking or a proposal to a government agency or local government agency. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 6 punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud kohustusliku ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise t&auml;htaeg ei v&otilde;i olla l&uuml;hem kui &uuml;ks kuu, arvates otsuse k&auml;ttesaamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The term for fulfilment of a mandatory precept specified in clauses (6) 2) or 3) of this section shall not be less than one month from the date of receipt of the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud kohustusliku ettekirjutusega kohustatakse ettev&otilde;tjat t&auml;itma &uuml;hte v&otilde;i mitut j&auml;rgnevatest kohustustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) One or several of the following obligations shall be imposed on an undertaking by a mandatory precept provided for in subsection (5) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) l&otilde;petada &otilde;iguserikkumine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to terminate the violation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taastada esialgne, enne &otilde;iguserikkumist eksisteerinud olukord; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to restore the situation which existed before the violation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teha tegusid k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to take actions to eliminate the violation of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) mitte ette v&otilde;tta toiminguid, mis v&otilde;ivad viia k&auml;esoleva seaduse n&otilde;uete rikkumisele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) not to perform acts which may lead to a violation of the requirements of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Juhtumi menetlemine l&otilde;petatakse Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega v&otilde;i seda ei alustata, kui selgub, et sama asi on esitatud kohtu menetlusse v&otilde;i kui selle kohta on juba j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Proceedings of a matter shall be terminated by a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy or shall not be commenced if it becomes evident that the same matter has been filed with a court or a court order in force concerning the matter already exists. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Konkurentsiamet avaldab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi alusel tehtud otsused kolme kuu jooksul, alates sellise otsuse j&otilde;ustumisest, v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hes &uuml;leriigilise levikuga p&auml;evalehes. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The Competition Board shall publish a decision made pursuant to this section within three months of the entry into force of such decision in at least one daily national newspaper. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;risaladuse hoidmise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to maintain business secrets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametil ei ole &otilde;igust avaldada ettev&otilde;tja n&otilde;usolekuta tema &auml;risaladusi teisele isikule ega neid avalikustada. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board does not have the right to disclose any business secrets of an undertaking to any other person or to make such business secrets public. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Auml;risaladuseks ei ole Konkurentsiametile esitatud kaebus ning juhtumi menetlemisega seotud v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja tegevuse kohta Konkurentsiameti peadirektori, ametniku v&otilde;i esindaja tehtud otsused, aktid v&otilde;i kokkuv&otilde;tted. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Complaints submitted to the Competition Board and decisions, reports and summaries relating to the proceedings of a matter or the activity of an undertaking made by the Director General of the Competition Board or any other official or representative of the Competition Board are not business secrets. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tete rikkumise tuvastamisel ei tohi Konkurentsiamet ettev&otilde;tja vastu kasutada teavet, mida k&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tete kohaselt ei saa sellele ettev&otilde;tjale avaldada. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon establishing a violation of any of the provisions of this Act, the Competition Board shall not use any information against an undertaking which, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, may not be disclosed to such undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Konkurentsiamet j&auml;tab k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel avaldamisele kuuluvate otsuste tekstist v&auml;lja &auml;risaladused. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Competition Board shall omit business secrets from the texts of decisions published pursuant to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus kohtu n&otilde;udmisel esitada kogu teave vastavale kohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Competition Board has the right to submit all information to a court at the request of the court. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for Violation of This Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise eest vastutavad: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following persons are held liable for violation of this Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) f&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud - haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku alusel ja </eesti>
<inglise>1) natural persons - pursuant to the Code of Administrative Offences; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juriidilised isikud - k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-de 43 ja 45 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) legal persons - pursuant to &sect;&sect; 43 and 45 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik rikub k&auml;esolevat seadust v&otilde;i sellest tulenevaid &otilde;igusakte, tegutsedes juriidilise isiku nimel v&otilde;i huvides, on &otilde;iguserikkumise eest vastutavad m&otilde;lemad ning haldusvastutust v&otilde;ib kohaldada nii juriidilisele kui ka f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a natural person acting on behalf of or in the interests of a legal person violates this Act or legislation arising therefrom, both persons are held liable for the violation and an administrative punishment may be imposed on both the legal person and the natural person </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juriidilisele isikule karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i sellest tulenevate &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise eest arvestatakse &otilde;iguserikkumise raskust, laadi ja teisi asjaolusid, rikkuja koost&ouml;&ouml;valmidust Konkurentsiametiga ning keelatud tegevuse l&otilde;petamist enne karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon imposition of a punishment for violation of this Act or legislation arising therefrom on a legal person, the gravity and nature of the violation and other circumstances, the extent of co-operation by the offender with the Competition Board and termination of the prohibited activity before the imposition of a punishment shall be considered. </inglise>
<eesti>Karistust ei kohaldata, kui &otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemisest v&otilde;i lepingu t&auml;itmise l&otilde;petamisest v&otilde;i kehtetuks muutumisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>No punishment is imposed if more than three years have passed from the violation or termination of performance of a contract or the contract becoming void. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus taotluse v&otilde;i otsuse mittet&auml;itmise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for non-fulfilment of request or decision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 27 ja 36-39 s&auml;testatud alusel Konkurentsiameti kirjalikus taotluses n&otilde;utud t&auml;htajaks teabe v&otilde;i materjalide p&otilde;hjendamatult mitteesitamise v&otilde;i tegutsemiskoha kontrollimise takistamise v&otilde;i Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja k&auml;skkirjaga etten&auml;htud kontrollist p&otilde;hjendamatu keeldumise v&otilde;i suulisele arutamisele p&otilde;hjendamatult mitteilmumise eest ettev&otilde;tja poolt on Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata ja vastuvaidlematus korras sisse n&otilde;uda rahatrahv kuni 2000 krooni iga kalendrip&auml;eva kohta alates trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast kuni ettev&otilde;tja poolt teabe kirjalikult Konkurentsiametile esitamise v&otilde;i kontrollimisele allumise p&auml;evani (viimane v&auml;lja arvatud). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an undertaking fails, without good reason, to submit information or materials by the deadline demanded in a written demand of the Competition Board on a basis provided for in &sect;&sect; 27 or 36-39 of this Act, prevents the inspection of the location of its activities, or, without good reason, refuses inspection prescribed by a directive of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy or fails to appear, without good reason, at an oral discussion, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may by a decision impose a fine of up to 2 000 kroons per calendar day, subject to mandatory collection as of the day following the date of imposition of the fine until the day the undertaking submits written information to the Competition Board or allows inspection (the last day excluded). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 40 l&otilde;ikes 6 s&auml;testatud Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsuses sisalduva kohustusliku ettekirjutuse mittet&auml;itmise v&otilde;i mitten&otilde;uetekohase t&auml;itmise korral ettev&otilde;tja poolt otsuses nimetatud p&auml;evaks on Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata ja vastuvaidlematus korras sisse n&otilde;uda rahatrahv kuni 5000 krooni iga kalendrip&auml;eva kohta alates trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast kuni ettev&otilde;tja poolt otsuses sisalduva ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise ja sellest Konkurentsiametile kirjalikult teatamise p&auml;evani (viimane v&auml;lja arvatud). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an undertaking fails to fulfil or unsatisfactorily fulfils a mandatory precept set out in a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy as provided for in subsection 40 (6) of this Act by the date specified in the decision, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may by a decision impose a fine of up to 5 000 kroons per calendar day, subject to mandatory collection as of the day following the date of imposition of the fine until the day the undertaking fulfils the precept set out in the decision and notifies the Competition Board thereof in writing (the last day excluded). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appeal of decisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 43 t&auml;hendatud Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja rahatrahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsuse peale on ettev&otilde;tjal &otilde;igus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus s&auml;testatud korras kaevata kohtusse &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates otsuse k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An undertaking has the right to file an appeal with a court against a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy on the imposition of a fine specified in &sect; 43 of this Act pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences within one month from the date such decision is received. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohtusse kaebamine peatab Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja rahatrahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsuse t&auml;itmise, kui kohus ei otsusta teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An appeal suspends execution of a decision on the imposition of a fine by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy, unless the court decides otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kohus otsustab, et Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsus on seaduslik, tasub ettev&otilde;tja rahatrahvi alates selle m&auml;&auml;ramisele j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast kuni kohtusse kaebamise p&auml;evani (viimane v&auml;lja arvatud) ja j&auml;tkab trahvi maksmist j&auml;rgmisest p&auml;evast p&auml;rast k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dumist kohtu otsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast kuni otsuses sisalduva n&otilde;udmise v&otilde;i ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise p&auml;evani (viimane v&auml;lja arvatud). </eesti>
<inglise>If the court rules that the decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy is lawful, the undertaking shall pay the fine as of the day following the date of imposition of the fine until the day the appeal was made (the last day excluded) and shall continue to pay the fine from the day following the passage of ten days from the entry into force of the court order until the day the requirement or precept set out in the decision is fulfilled (the last day excluded). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui kohus tunnistab Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsuse seadusevastaseks, tagastatakse sissen&otilde;utud trahvisumma trahvi maksnud ettev&otilde;tjale kohtu poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the court rules that the decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy is unlawful, the collected fine shall be returned to the undertaking which paid the fine, to the extent determined by the court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku vastutus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of legal person for administrative offence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametile eba&otilde;ige, mittet&auml;ieliku v&otilde;i eksitava teabe esitamise v&otilde;i &uuml;hinemisest mitteteatamise v&otilde;i mittet&auml;htaegse teatamise eest m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv suuruses kuni &uuml;ks protsent trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud seaduserikkuja majandusaasta realiseerimise netok&auml;ibest, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For submission of incorrect, incomplete or misleading information or for failure to give notice of a merger or to give notice of a merger on time to the Competition Board, a fine of up to 1 per cent of the net turnover of the financial year of the offender preceding the year that the decision to impose a fine is made shall be imposed, but not less than 10 000 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel keelatud koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse, keelatud kokkuleppe j&otilde;ustamise, erandit vajavale kokkuleppele selle s&otilde;lmimisest kuue kuu jooksul erandi taotlemata j&auml;tmise, erandiotsuses m&auml;&auml;ratud tingimuse v&otilde;i kohustuse mittet&auml;itmise, kaubaturul valitseva ettev&otilde;tja seisundi kuritarvitamise v&otilde;i vastava tegevuse kavandamise eest m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv suuruses kuni viis protsenti trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud seaduserikkuja majandusaasta realiseerimise netok&auml;ibest, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui 20 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For concerted practices, enforcement of a prohibited agreement, failure to apply for an exemption for an agreement which requires exemption within six months from entry into such agreement, failure to fulfil a condition or obligation established in a decision of exemption, for abuse of a dominant position of an undertaking in the market or for planning such acts, a fine of up to 5 per cent of the net turnover of the financial year of the offender preceding the year that the decision to impose a fine is made shall be imposed, but not less than 20 000 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igusi omavale ettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;i loomulikule monopolile k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 18 s&auml;testatud kohustuste mittet&auml;itmise eest m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv suuruses kuni &uuml;ks protsent trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud seaduserikkuja majandusaasta realiseerimise netok&auml;ibest, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For failure to fulfil the obligations provided for in &sect; 18 of this Act imposed on an undertaking with special or exclusive rights or a natural monopoly, a fine of up to 1 per cent of the net turnover of the financial year of the offender preceding the year that the decision to impose a fine is made shall be imposed, but not less than 10 000 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahviga s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste eest karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on halduskohtunikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Administrative judges have the right to impose punishments for the administrative offences provided for in this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation of minutes of administrative offences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektoril, tema aset&auml;itjal, osakonnajuhatajal ja tema aset&auml;itjal ning peaspetsialistil on &otilde;igus koostada protokoll k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 45 s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General, his or her deputy, department heads, deputy department heads and chief specialists of the Competition Board have the right to prepare reports of administrative offences provided for in &sect; 45 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud protokolli v&otilde;ib mitte teha, kui olukord kaubaturul on parandatud ja kahjud, kui need tekkisid, on heastatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A report specified in subsection (1) of this section need not be prepared if the situation in the market has been remedied and the losses, if any, have been compensated for. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud protokoll peab sisaldama j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A report specified in subsection (1) of this section shall include the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of preparation thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) selle asutuse nimetus ja aadress, mille nimel protokoll koostatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and address of the agency in whose name the report is prepared; </inglise>
<eesti>3) protokolli koostanud isiku ametinimetus, ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the official title and the given name and surname of the person who prepared the report; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja nimetus v&otilde;i &auml;rinimi, registreerimise number ja asukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name or business name, registration number and seat of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>5) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the given name, surname and office of the representative of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>6) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise koht, aeg ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the place, time and description of the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) viide k&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tetele, mille alusel haldusvastutust kohaldatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a reference to the provisions of this Act which are the basis for imposition of administrative liability; </inglise>
<eesti>8) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja seletus v&otilde;i m&auml;rge seletuse andmisest loobumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>8) an explanation provided by the representative of the administrative offender or a notation concerning refusal to provide an explanation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Protokollile kirjutavad alla selle koostanud isik ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja v&otilde;i tema esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The person who prepares the report and the administrative offender or his or her representative shall sign the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja v&otilde;i tema esindaja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse sellesse vastav kanne. </eesti>
<inglise>If the administrative offender or his or her representative refuses to sign the report, a corresponding entry shall be made therein. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile lisatakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja v&otilde;i tema esindaja kirjalikud m&auml;rkused protokolli, samuti protokollile allakirjutamisest keeldumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Written notations of the administrative offender or his or her representative concerning the report and on refusal to sign the report shall be appended to the report. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings in matters concerning administrative offences </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlus k&auml;esoleva seadusega s&auml;testatud juriidilise isiku &otilde;iguserikkumise asjas toimub haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 95, 843; 2000, 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301 ja 305) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 61, 981; 103, 1695; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222) s&auml;testatud korras, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei n&auml;e ette teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning administrative offences by legal persons provided for in this Act are conducted pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 95, 843; 2000, 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301 ja 305) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 61, 981; 103, 1695; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222), unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahjude h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for damage </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seadusega keelatud tegude toimepanemisega tekitatud varaline v&otilde;i muu kahju kuulub h&uuml;vitamisele tsiviilkorras. </eesti>
<inglise>Proprietary or other damage caused by actions prohibited by this Act shall be compensated for by way of civil procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>11. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. &sect; 27.Amendments to Code of Administrative Offences </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku paragrahv 228 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 16 s&auml;testatud viited muudetakse ja s&otilde;nastatakse j&auml;rgmiselt "1372, 159 lg. 1". </eesti>
<inglise>The references specified in clause 228 (1) 16) of the Code of Administrative Offences are amended and worded as follows: "&sect; 137 (2), subsection 159 (1)". </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;riseadustiku t&auml;iendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to Commercial Code </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;riseadustikku t&auml;iendatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>The Commercial Code is amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) paragrahvi 393 l&otilde;iget 2 t&auml;iendatakse tekstiga: </eesti>
<inglise>1) the following text is added to subsection 393 (2): </inglise>
<eesti>&ldquo;, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui &uuml;hinevate &auml;ri&uuml;hingute majandusaasta reali-seerimise netok&auml;ive &uuml;letab sada miljonit krooni v&otilde;i &uuml;hinevad &auml;ri-&uuml;hingud saavutavad enam kui 40 protsenti kaubaturust"; </eesti>
<inglise>&ldquo;, with the exception of cases where the realised net turnover of the merging commercial undertakings for the financial year exceeds one hundred million kroons or the merging commercial undertakings have control over more than 40 per cent of the market"; </inglise>
<eesti>2) paragrahvi 400 l&otilde;iget 1 t&auml;iendatakse punktiga 9 j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>2) subsection 400 (1) is amended by adding clause 9) worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"9) Konkurentsiameti kinnitus &uuml;hinemise kohta kogu vajaliku teabe saamisest, kui &uuml;hinevate &auml;ri&uuml;hingute majandusaasta reali-seerimise netok&auml;ive &uuml;letab sada miljonit krooni v&otilde;i &uuml;hinevad &auml;ri-&uuml;hingud saavutavad enam kui 40 protsenti kaubaturust." </eesti>
<inglise>"9) the confirmation from the Competition Board of receipt of all necessary information concerning the merger, if the realised net turnover of the merging commercial undertakings for the financial year exceeds one hundred million kroons or the merging commercial undertakings have control over more than 40 per cent of the market. &ldquo;. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse k&otilde;igi konkurentsivabadust kahjustavate kokkulepete ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuste suhtes, mis kehtivad k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise hetkel ja mis teostatakse p&auml;rast seda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act applies to all agreements and concerted practices which restrict competition and are in force at the moment of entry into force of this Act and which are carried out thereafter. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eranditaotlus seoses kokkuleppega, mis s&otilde;lmiti enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist, loetakse esitatuks k&auml;esolevas seaduses m&auml;rgitud t&auml;htaegu &uuml;letamata, kui see esitatakse Konkurentsiametile kuue kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for exemption concerning an agreement entered into before the entry into force of this Act is deemed to be submitted without exceeding the deadline specified in this Act if it is submitted to the Competition Board within six months after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusminister teeb 1996. ja 1997. aasta riigiabi andmise aruande 1999. aasta jooksul vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 25. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance shall make a report concerning the grant of state aid in 1996 and 1997 during 1999 pursuant to &sect; 25 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Repeal of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Tunnistatakse kehtetuks konkurentsiseadus (RT 1993, 47, 642; 1995, 26-28, 355; 1996, 49, 953). </eesti>
<inglise>The Competition Act (RT 1993, 47, 642; 1995, 26-28, 355; 1996, 49, 953) is repealed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into force of Act </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus j&otilde;ustub 1998. aasta 1. oktoobril. </eesti>
